OK, curiosity killed the t-cat.  When we do `buildah images --format ...`  we do this after each image:

```
        if terminal.IsTerminal(int(os.Stdout.Fd())) {
                fmt.Println()
        }
```
at https://github.com/projectatomic/buildah/blob/master/cmd/buildah/images.go#L403.  In the bats environment where the tests run, there's no associated tty so the carriage return is not printed out and the end result is one line of images jammed together, that's why the format test failed checking for mor than one line as expected.  In a standard terminal, it returns two lines.

@rhatdan @nalind @umohnani8 unless you can think of a reason to keep this term check, I'm going to remove it.  It seems to work fine in both a standard terminal and in the bats tests without it.
